<p>I have two tables :</p>  <pre><code>create table a ( `1` array&lt;string&gt;);  create table b ( `1` array&lt;int&gt;); </code></pre>  <p>and I want to put the table a in table b (table b is empty) :</p>  <pre><code>insert into table b select * from a; </code></pre>  <p>when doing so I get the following error : </p>  <pre><code>FAILED: SemanticException [Error 10044]: Line 1:18 Cannot insert into target table because column number/types are different 'b': Cannot convert column 0 from array&lt;string&gt; to array&lt;int&gt;. </code></pre>  <p>whereas I would not get this error if the fields were only of types <code>string</code> and <code>int</code>.</p>  <p>Is there a way to do the cast with arrays ?</p>